      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            The population of a city, <m>P</m>, in millions, is a function of <m>t</m>, the number of
            years since 1960, so <m>P = f(t)</m>. Which of the following statements explains the
            meaning of <m>f(38) = 8</m> in terms of the population of this city?
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  The population of this city in the year 38 is 8 million people.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  The population of this city in the year 8 is 38 million people.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  The population of this city in the year 1968 is 38 million people.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  The population of this city in the year 1998 is 8 million people.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            The independent variable is the number of years after 1960 so the <q>38</q> represents
            the year 1998. Hence, the phrase <q>The population of this city in the year 1998 is 8
            million people</q> is the correct phrase.
          </p>
        </solution>
