      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Determine the slope and <m>y</m>-intercept of the line whose equation is <m>-4y + 6x + 8 =
            0</m>.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Solving for <m>y</m> we see that
            <me>
              4y = 6x + 8  \implies  y = \frac{6}{4} x + 2.
            </me>
          </p>

          <p>
            Therefore the slope is <m>m=\frac{6}{4} = \frac{3}{2}</m> and the <m>y</m>-intercept is <m>2</m>.
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
