            The value of a car in 1990 is <dollar />13,100 and the value is expected to go down by <dollar />80
            per year for the next 7 years. Write a linear function for the value, <m>V</m>, of the
            1990 car as a function of the number of years from 1990, <m>x</m>.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <me>
            V(x) = -80x + 13100
          </me>
        </solution>
